Summary: Ammendment to 19443; Not Sure of ISS Theory.
divs: sighting detailsfrom my phone log, i refine my sighting (#19443) time from 19:50 to 19:45. a more recent case speculates that what we all saw was the international space station. nasa's website provides times and directions that one can view the iss. i went to the site(http:\\spaceflight.nasa.gov\realdata\sightings\cities\view.cgi?country=united_states®ion=virginia&city=falls_church) and compared the data to my own observations and they don't match. nasa's data is as follows: sat sep 19\09:05 pm < 1 11 10 above nnw 11 above n. nasa says that the sighting should have occured at 21:05; mine was at 19:45. nasa said that the max elevation of the sighting should have been 11 degrees; mine was approximately 30. nasa said that the approach angle would be 10 degrees above nnw and the departure direction would be 11 degrees above n; my sighting was se and stationary. based on nasa's data, i don't have a great degree of confidence that it was the iss.
